tasks.task: Starting vegetable seeds indoors in February
subtasks: Gather supplies
Prepare seed trays with high quality seed starting mix
Plant tomato seeds a quarter inch deep
Place seed trays in bright window or use grow lights
Maintain consistent moisture for germination
Provide adequate light (6 hours/day for tomatoes)
Transition tomato seedlings to outdoor conditions gradually
Plant pepper seeds (sweet or spicy varieties) a quarter inch deep
Maintain temperature around 70-80°F using heat mat if needed
Provide 14-16 hours of light for pepper seedlings
Encourage sturdy stem development with gentle brushing
Water pepper seedlings to maintain consistent moisture
Plant eggplant seeds a quarter inch deep
Maintain consistent temperature of around 75°F with heating mat
Provide bright, indirect sunlight for eggplant seedlings
Sow broccoli seeds about half inch deep in a well-draining mix
Maintain temperature between 60-65°F for broccoli seedlings
Ensure consistent moisture for broccoli
Check for pests and diseases, provide adequate light
Sow cauliflower seeds about half inch deep
Maintain cooler temperatures (60-65°F) for cauliflower seedlings
Ensure consistent moisture and prevent waterlogging
Start lettuce seeds a quarter inch deep
Maintenance of temperature and moisture for lettuce
Provide bright indirect light for all seedlings
Start spinach seeds a half inch deep
Maintain cool temperatures (60-70°F) for spinach
Water to keep soil consistently moist but not soggy
Start kale seeds a half inch deep
Maintain cool temperatures (60-70°F) and moist soil
